<HEADLINE>
<P>
SLOUCHING TOWARD THE MILLENNIUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your collection of predictions was interesting but largely superficial and 
insular. Mention of the interconnectedness of our country and the world was 
minimal, and nothing was written that addressed the basic problem: too many 
people. Too many people seeking the high standard of living now enjoyed by the 
few developed nations, and those few already too many in relation to 
consumption of world resources. 
</P>
<P>
WILLARD OLNEY, Hesperia 
</P>
</TEXT>
