COLLEGE NEWS: NURSING SCHOLARSHIPS GO TO 9 AT AZUSA PACIFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nine Azusa Pacific University nursing students have been awarded $1,000 
scholarships by the Kaiser Permanente Scholarship Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
They are Elizabeth Argandona of Diamond Bar; Jaqueline Ismail of Beaver Falls, 
Pa.; Terry Labansat of Sunland; Lisa Lee of Hacienda Heights; Ellen Mandani of 
La Verne; Tina Morrison of West Covina; Bernard Prouty of Seal Beach; Shelly 
Salse of Azusa, and Arlene Vander Dussen of Chino. 
