<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE NEWS: $140,000 IN FELLOWSHIPS FOR WOMEN AT CALTECH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Caltech has won a $144,000 grant for three, two-year Clare Booth Luce Graduate 
Fellowships for female students. 
</P>
<P>
The grants will be used by women pursuing Ph.D. degrees in physics, mathematics 
and astronomy; chemistry and chemical engineering; engineering and applied 
science, or geological and planetary sciences. 
</P>
<P>
They are provided by the Clare Boothe Luce Fund, which was created to encourage 
women to enter, study, graduate and teach in scientific and technological 
fields in which women are under-represented. 
</P>
</TEXT>
