<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE NEWS: 2 SCHOOLS RECEIVE JOINT $500,000 KNIGHT GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Claremont McKenna College and Pomona College have received a joint $500,000 
grant from the Knight Foundation of Akron, Ohio, as part of the Foundation's 
Excellence in Undergraduate Education program. 
</P>
<P>
The grant will be matched by the two schools and used for projects such as a 
campuswide fiber-optic computer network that links students and faculty to 
library databases and off-campus centers. 
</P>
<P>
The Knight Foundation was established by John S. Knight and James L. Knight, 
founders of the Knight-Ridder Inc. newspaper chain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
