<P>
27TH GOLD NUGGET COMPETITION SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Pacific Coast Builders Conference (PCBC) has issued a call for architects, 
builders, developers and land planners to participate in its 27th annual Gold 
Nugget -- Best in the West -- Awards competition. 
</P>
<P>
Completed entries must be submitted by April 11. 
</P>
<P>
The competition this year includes more land-use design categories and a "new 
town" category, according to Joe Pickett Jr., Gold Nugget Awards chairman. 
</P>
<P>
The competition is open to all residential, commercial and industrial 
developments -- including remodeling and renovation projects -- and those in 
the site-planning stages in the 14 western states including Texas. 
</P>
<P>
Awards will be presented on June 14 during the PCBC in San Francisco. Entry 
forms and information are available from: Gold Nugget Awards, PCBC, 605 Market 
St., Suite 600, San Francisco, Calif. 94105. The telephone number is (415) 
543-2600. 
</P>
