<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOVIET OFFICER KILLED IN ETHIOPIAN PLANE CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, Ethiopia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ethiopia said Friday that the head of the Soviet military mission here and four 
senior Ethiopian army officers had been killed in a helicopter crash in the 
eastern province of Harerge. 
</P>
<P>
The official Ethiopian News Agency said that 17 people, including six Soviets, 
died when the helicopter smashed into the side of a mountain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021190-0107 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 174822 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 11, 1990, Sunday, Bulldog Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 29; Column 1; Advance Desk 
</P>
