<HEADLINE>
<P>
UPGRADE AIRPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego has become a world center for the biotechnology industry. In the 12 
years since I co-founded Hybritech, more than 70 companies have started here. 
</P>
<P>
The biotechnology industry is one that is built on strategic alliances with 
other U.S., European and Japanese companies. This requires our partners to 
visit us and us to visit them. In order for us to compete, we must have 
efficient air service. San Diego does not have a first-class airport, nor 
first-class air service. To get to any major city on the East Coast, Japan or 
Europe, one must always go through connections. This uses valuable time, and 
time is money. 
</P>
<P>
The United States is currently the leader in biotechnology, and if we are to 
stay that way and establish San Diego as a global industry center, we must make 
the decision today to upgrade our airport and air service. If we don't, this 
industry, which employs thousands of people and generates an ever-increasing 
tax base, will not be able to continue in this city and county. 
</P>
<P>
The decision-makers in this community must form a business plan to improve our 
air service and meet the travel demands of their constituents -- now. In a few 
years it will be too late. 
</P>
<P>
HOWARD C. BIRNDORF 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
