<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE GOOD IGNORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The news media are blowing out of proportion gang happenings and painting the 
wrong picture of Southeast San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
For all the drive-by shootings, there are as many good things happening, such 
as the Regional Youth Center that provides summer jobs for the low-income 
families. The Palace, formerly called the Boys' Club, provides recreational 
activities and dance parties on the weekends. The Bandini Center is a 
continuation program that helps students make up classes. 
</P>
<P>
Southeast San Diego is not always as the newspaper and TV describe it. I live 
there and I like it. 
</P>
<P>
FREDDRICK BROWN 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
