<HEADLINE>
<P>
ST. LOUIS MAN KILLS 2 STEPSONS, WOUNDS SELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ST. LOUIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man took his two young stepsons hostage Friday after a dispute with his 
estranged wife, then fatally shot the boys and wounded himself in the shoulder, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
The man was identified as 28-year-old Marcus Atkins. He was listed in stable 
condition at St. Louis University Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Police broke down the apartment door after hearing shots and found the dead 
boys, ages 8 and 5. 
</P>
