<HEADLINE>
<P>
THIS WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RODEO DRIVE: The Flying U Rodeo will celebrate its 61st year of continuous 
rodeo roughhousing by returning to the Long Beach Arena Saturday with 
performances at 1 and 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
SOCIO-POLITICAL DEBATE: Phyllis Schlafly, a leading woman in American 
conservative politics, and Sarah Weddington, a leader in women's rights 
advocacy for the past 15 years, will meet at Whittier College on Thursday to 
debate "The Changing Roles of Men and Women." 
</P>
