<P>
Table, THE PRICES PEOPLE WILL PAY, VINTAGE ; Table, THE PRICES PEOPLE WILL PAY, 
CONTEMPORARY ; Photo, Attorney Michael Whalen bought photographic art for nine 
floors of his partnership's offices for less than $300,000 -- but the day of 
such a relative bargain may be over. JIM MENDENHALL / L.A. Times; Photo, G. Ray 
Hawkins, a leading photo dealer, reports his best quarter ever. ROSEMARY KAUL / 
L.A. Times; Photo, Ansel Adams' "Moonrise, Hernandez, N.M.": $35,750 in 1989. ; 
Photo, Man Ray's 1924 "Le Violon d'Ingres": More than $100,000. ; Photo, A 
detail of the Starn Twins' "Lisa": $32,000. ; Photo, COLOR, (Cover) The Cover: 
A decade made a world of difference in the prices paid at auction for prints of 
Edward Weston's "Shell" (1927). Details about the famed photographer and this 
photograph on Page 9a. 
</P>
