<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOUGLAS KOS TYSON IN TITLE FIGHT UPSET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
James (Buster) Douglas knocked out heavyweight champion Mike Tyson in the 10th 
round at the Tokyo Dome today in one of the biggest upsets in boxing history. 
</P>
<P>
Douglas, 29, the fourth-ranked contender, felled the previously unbeaten 
champion with a five-punch combination to the head at 1:23 of the round. 
</P>
<P>
Tyson rolled over at the count of five and reached for his mouthpiece. He was 
on his hands and knees when the referee counted him out. 
</P>
<P>
Tyson, who was 37-0 with 33 knockouts going into the fight, was such a 
prohibitive favorite that Las Vegas refused to put up a betting line. Douglas 
now is 30-4-1. 
</P>
<P>
Breaking down in tears while draped with the title belts that have belonged to 
Tyson since 1986, Douglas said the reason he won was "my mother," referring to 
the recent death of Lula Pearl Douglas. 
</P>
<P>
Full coverage in Sports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Mike Tyson reels from a blow by James (Buster) Douglas, who knocked out 
the previously undefeated heavyweight champ in Tokyo. Reuters 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
