<P>
PERSIAN GULF; 
</P>
<P>
PAPERS ASSAIL SOVIET EMIGRATION POLICIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Persian Gulf newspapers renewed criticism of Moscow over the emigration of 
Soviet Jews to Israel, and accused the superpowers of striking a deal to settle 
them in the occupied Palestinian territories. One Saudi Arabian newspaper, 
Al-Riyadh, claimed there was "an international conspiracy to increase tension 
in the Arab situation." Up to 100,000 Soviet Jews are expected to emigrate to 
Israel this year although the Jewish state says it has no policy of settling 
them in the occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip. 
</P>
