<TEXT>
<P>
An 11-year-old boy who allegedly threatened to beat up five elementary school 
classmates unless they turned over their milk money has been arrested and 
charged with felony extortion, authorities said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The boy, who admitted taking the money, was released to the custody of his 
mother, officials said. He was suspended from school for three days and may 
face expulsion, the principal said. 
</P>
