<P>
SIGHTSEEING COPTER CRASHES IN RIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A helicopter on a sightseeing trip around Manhattan and carrying four tourists 
and a pilot went down in the East River, bursting into flames after it crashed 
into the water near a helipad, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Police divers and a rescuer in a life raft aided the passengers and pilot, with 
some of the survivors holding onto a board extended by the boater until help 
arrived, witnesses said. Eight people, including three rescuers, were taken to 
the hospital. A 14-year-old boy on the helicopter was in critical condition 
after his heart stopped, police said. Authorities said they were investigating 
the crash. 
</P>
