DEPUTIES RESPONDING TO CALL KILL MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was shot to death Saturday night by Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies 
after they were summoned to a quiet residential neighborhood in Lynwood to 
break up a dispute between two men, investigators said. 
</P>
<P>
Details were sketchy. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting occurred at 7:18 p.m. in the 3500 block of Brenton Avenue. 
Neighbors reported hearing at least four shots. One woman said the unidentified 
dead man apparently was shot in a scuffle with deputies after refusing orders 
to lie on the ground. 
</P>
<P>
The Sheriff's Department has been criticized by blacks after the shooting death 
by a deputy of a Nation of Islam member who allegedly had taken the deputy's 
gun. The victim Saturday night was described by witnesses only as a middle-aged 
white male. 
</P>
