<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified man died late Saturday in a house fire in the 900 block of 
Buffalo Avenue, firefighters said. 
</P>
<P>
Details of the single-alarm blaze were sketchy, but firefighters said they 
believe the victim was in the house alone. 
</P>
<P>
A neighbor called the Fire Department at 10:03 p.m., according to Santa Ana 
fire dispatcher Mike Gates. 
</P>
<P>
Three engines, two trucks and a paramedic unit responded, he said. The cause of 
the fire was under investigation, Gates said. 
