<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLIDAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Monday is Lincoln's Birthday. The following will be closed in observance of the 
holiday: 
</P>
<P>
All county and state offices. 
</P>
<P>
Most public elementary, junior and high schools, except for those in the 
following districts: Los Alamitos Unified, Saddleback Valley Unified and Santa 
Ana Unified. 
</P>
<P>
All colleges and universities, including community colleges, will be open. 
</P>
<P>
County and state courthouses. 
</P>
<P>
County libraries. 
</P>
<P>
City offices in Brea, Costa Mesa, Irvine, Laguna Niguel and San Juan Capistrano 
will be closed. All others will be open. 
</P>
<P>
Federal offices and courthouses will be open. 
</P>
<P>
All banks and savings and loans will be open. 
</P>
<P>
Mail: All post offices will be open and mail will be delivered. 
</P>
<P>
Trash: There will be regular trash pickup by city and county refuse workers. 
</P>
<P>
Buses: Orange County Transit District buses will run on regular schedules. 
There will be dial-a-ride and car-pool services available on the holiday. 
</P>
<P>
Parks: All city- and county-run parks and recreation facilities will be open 
during regular hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
